CGTN breaks down the reasons behind the United States reaching its tragic milestone this month – 1 million deaths. Was it COVID-19 alone that was responsible? Something else spread as fast – disinformation. Politicians and some media fanned ignorance, encouraging anti-vaxxers and anti-mask activists. The healthcare industry sought to profit from people's suffering, following "a model of greed". And racism led to greater deaths among African-Americans, Latin Americans and native Americans. The ordeal is not over yet. In May, new cases have started spiking again. Is there a cure? Watch the show to find out.  